{"_id":"0sRUBUKdIfuEapLk","name":"Hanse","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5Zrq5DSeaUWZGMkj","name":"Hanse - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","positive":"I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vxRdfKKXaT668tCt","name":"Gift - Mutant Maw","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9KT4vRJeIJaboTv6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-hanse-101","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":101,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1LU78xZ9wRJAgnvb","name":"Crazed Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"uZrSfy4LZCljC0sS","name":"Crazed Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","positive":"A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9ExnJm3hevBKySYl","name":"Gift - Mutant Abomination","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YWPKluzEQTADJDV7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-crazed-maws-102","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":102,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eat every living thing, except other Maws.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2z7dF091hEgGkk6r","name":"Hedge Labyrinth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"y0YerOpefrmKzxrI","name":"Hedge Labyrinth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","positive":"A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r9OL5faa5reaFer6","name":"Gift - Secret Passage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"b2fWt81kExPFvjVD","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-hedge-labyrinth-129","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":129,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"36Z1BHsZ8LEnDMgf","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"t9w3bXeo9QFInlnx","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7E5eYV8sCaqOXzYE","name":"Gift - Latent Witch","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PcrTASuBExNdGFVp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bruna-the-poor-witch-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3XANKF9oPVfgjyqp","name":"Bella’s Servants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qQkr7ufeWttJa745","name":"Bella’s Servants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Z3zdJYr4H7gsub4l","name":"Gift - For Our Lady","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bVq8bOiq0Uudm4QC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-servants-127","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":127,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5XEyVW05EwvDvOm5","name":"Aleksandr Pták","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5dvUDtB0MRrBgfY2","name":"Aleksandr Pták - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yD6xEWnvFzBP8SxN","name":"Gift - Swallow’s Flight","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ruzn4nprCzdQv4w5","name":"Gift - What is Yours is Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vExBfULSPvsPz14d","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-aleksandr-pt-k-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5sf2sa1BL6TPhjQc","name":"Arne the Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0eTc8DjRFLTptLxG","name":"Arne the Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kSIlUR1DSiZL1pYd","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-arne-the-captain-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7moweb3lakst027s","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0NnYYBPAk5H6v41D","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sKpjXaf9YwmwXRyQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-mercenary-and-researcher-of-renowned-fame-139","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":139,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8Sis9tPhtp1ad32h","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"5stJ5deOucBcjIpM","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UAVWcUxmwrzuV8do","name":"Gift - Seals Everywhere","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LqWk519l7dKB1wcr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-seal-of-the-cauldron-fae-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Axj5S4ZXdBNtMwqW","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pL6kMfOGjgmCpXRg","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","positive":"I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"07CVUpiT6lpSeQc1","name":"Gift - Agent of the Order","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PuGh6ZUoD7IritPw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-althea-the-agent-of-the-order-99","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":99,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BhqIT5i6j4eEMU4N","name":"Talia the Sleeper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OTY9HDlIiuOJdzWZ","name":"Talia the Sleeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lxg22KcLMcAKSRAE","name":"Gift - Sleeping Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UyCa5tnOggHju3kZ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-talia-the-sleeper-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E4thHxU24DMKBcjx","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Q1DzS1sL8qI1CnKr","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smQSNiZvsGwpWh9T","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-count-azul-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EOhiwVbwk3tBSATI","name":"Ostromir Malý","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ePo5hRRBbPhlrnKt","name":"Ostromir Malý - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"I4qCtyJFoBBeYaMR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-ostromir-mal-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FaMGvGQBVQr3gyS9","name":"Nature Rises Up","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"v7gpNO9TWLz7EYan","name":"Nature Rises Up - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nWKNO1L19tKkpH2u","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-nature-rises-up-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FaUuRuYnM40gvpT8","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"xnsQsB5RLk0eom5r","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","positive":"We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V4dZzI201IN4xNQD","name":"Gift - The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RafpHmj6TC7QMIc8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-francisca-and-marta-the-vengeful-sisters-157","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":157,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FxfgNMMiWALQdDwe","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kUxdiLNGAGDAIHCW","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1s0t1KveqH0bavht","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-pietro-gonsalva-regent-of-capodimonte-125","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":125,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IbkEWPGQlm3LQ22J","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1yKSugmpoEPv8lzy","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HWMnvrryHnhwQJpr","name":"Gift - The Ruby of Hate","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qZ9tSKaElkIDaOa5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-cernobog-potme-il-the-child-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzC7Qbc2FXzmUU2L","name":"Lisbet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Pmf2llejd0ACr2pu","name":"Lisbet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ReitLbLs1fJwDcs1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-lisbet-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzG9GpTHpv1ztm4Z","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1xjq9hLrCvQTcFZa","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168.","positive":"I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lQRpeiMk94WkCxJf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-georg-slanina-the-helper-168","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":168,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JWJCA3Pc9ABKVllm","name":"Akim the Tamer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mxuRidMcVy91cYIH","name":"Akim the Tamer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VyTAIyfjwtqMHqhI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-akim-the-tamer-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JjhywroInzrid2j7","name":"The Doves","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"txCqaVKbLWh90dN3","name":"The Doves - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","positive":"We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BRdjHVbvlE5SsdHy","name":"Gift - Go for the Eyes","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2HtGmSl6Sr0H2Xua","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-doves-155","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":155,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KAi3KmZt2mF0k7Es","name":"George Carnarvon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PSoO96E8aCTIrGHA","name":"George Carnarvon - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ig92uT0R44Z3jPPj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-george-carnarvon-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KMDFSJCSijRBspFr","name":"Pack of Mastiffs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"awn9bFcy3Nah50N3","name":"Pack of Mastiffs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No \none can escape our sense of smell.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No \none can escape our sense of smell.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xH6epIJLfoUMwbh2","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No \none can escape our sense of smell.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-pack-of-mastiffs-127","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":127,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No \none can escape our sense of smell.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MDneQMpkrawIQYAi","name":"Georg the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"753psErBEub0wng1","name":"Georg the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tbpoIN3rcjAf7XrS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-georg-the-survivor-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MSlkQ7k9UhlLPZe3","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"nEkmJsqQzbqfy7oT","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130.","positive":"I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"F5yC9R5kmhjoPuYO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dioniso-gonsalva-called-the-beast-130","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":130,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PthHXRiJUYJdGSzL","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"E6k4gyKMgC8447Os","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Igapo7f1Bp9Yv7LV","name":"Gift - Gang Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CmMngv5O4K7k0yCq","name":"Gift - Rioter","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"i8FwIcX5aAi3sOoY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-the-gang-of-the-lost-boys-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"S3fURzRdz5ipCa6j","name":"Abel the Young Lover","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pJAvRNB6Moi8x64b","name":"Abel the Young Lover - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112.","positive":"I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xZ16QXDaMmes9FY8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-abel-the-young-lover-112","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":112,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TYiUc3rDgAsvl9ql","name":"The Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3xz1HbsCKa17aLDo","name":"The Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97.","positive":"We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z9gpQYAKbQqby9cg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-the-maws-97","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":97,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"URi5ONWolZT4U8MV","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"y3BoedlEwO8OQFOT","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1HKiPajEOltlavKu","name":"Gift - Pack","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U7alNb0sLTD3bTx5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dionysus-mastiffs-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UwJ9K9me766rPKkG","name":"Bianca Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"B4jFoLwr2RmuVxB5","name":"Bianca Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117.","positive":"I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P2UVH5puSyrie5rW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bianca-karenmann-117","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":117,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VzJj6uGlV9WJt1Nd","name":"Eduardo and Felipe","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7kDmSX2ZYYQfBaX","name":"Eduardo and Felipe - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156.","positive":"We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pho3DT6zVuNtQVj3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-eduardo-and-felipe-156","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":156,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WERs78LDIHfbhvvp","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Silaool8thDbBCPd","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CfmyexPWOB6buiQA","name":"Gift - The Solver","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0jAV0kjUIvUtX7MR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-svenn-the-skilled-hunter-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XNJjucfR3Pvv7jAW","name":"Alexandra the Mother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"JRTjGNGreb3z8UqR","name":"Alexandra the Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"X6BnZpqksgmuVFZL","name":"Gift - Deformed Orc","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"S4Sf0i6CdeX0VoPo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-alexandra-the-mother-142","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":5},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XPKGOCVwuWfgjRqr","name":"Berto the Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"iInoOXu3yScnWPUB","name":"Berto the Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smeRW1vCHocIMIka","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-berto-the-bear-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XlLWIGkRCJ4NcRJ0","name":"Pietrik","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jY0Hestx4CSH76E1","name":"Pietrik - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","positive":"I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XuLguQgtNmtIjNCP","name":"Gift - The Needle of Living Shadows","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zgyMKjdlKgZkYyHg","name":"Gift - Personal Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yLoQGQAiQbFfzXqg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-pietrik-87","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":87,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XpSypIhKHdJvmhrg","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"vzANKQeXKtmk6IQZ","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h80U6Xnf4KmuzdGW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-mtyrya-the-fairy-also-called-the-cauldron-fae-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YGXVCaLUGypKyAbF","name":"Father Cristoforo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qblMo68mazYndcf9","name":"Father Cristoforo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fzJSK0zg8qrD0xbN","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-father-cristoforo-126","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":126,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YwnmImWpaqtQKbmb","name":"Bella’s Handmaids","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"eZO5HGpVvrpPB1pp","name":"Bella’s Handmaids - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CrITrc1MmQfR5YSv","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-handmaids-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a4tN8nbbmkfHjcXj","name":"Princesca of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"sxgGlpRsthsr7y7Z","name":"Princesca of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pi1xkCoEcYzZypUq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-princesca-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cExnTGYOM4HyjllW","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CPUpieqhBt6JK0cH","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","positive":"I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QMrpL9mGKDn5Ytwq","name":"Gift - The Secrets of Metal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals).</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r2pZOPZTbuMXMIyu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-konstantin-svoboda-the-alchemist-167","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":167,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dJyeQkZti2sYRcVz","name":"Tasha the Tiger","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Mo7GBOjHIeAFJnD7","name":"Tasha the Tiger - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8XMWL1rYW26DOWct","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-tasha-the-tiger-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dkxYuUu36dRYwqUF","name":"Director of the Theater","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KPmiwJFNSdXaLFEW","name":"Director of the Theater - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171.","positive":"I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fFoCmcc81sMthtDo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-director-of-the-theater-171","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":171,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dodxEP8aviLbmldH","name":"The Food of the Gods","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ElOXsSj7ahBcS3Oz","name":"The Food of the Gods - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LFDklJZfp4EYWMYZ","name":"Gift - The Drug of the True Self","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQV6s2UCVhZpLWiV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-the-food-of-the-gods-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"f68iqkEfz2pFZdQj","name":"Basil the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"IdorBfLfppY6vCXN","name":"Basil the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86.","positive":"I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AgBweE1XwW4xxm6a","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-basil-the-survivor-86","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":86,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fAeubWQlsAkoppa2","name":"Gwendolyn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7ojmkbYhxPLdB5t2","name":"Gwendolyn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h8ARL1pXNi4FsWmm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-gwendolyn-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gZhFNSOgQvktKjb8","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FHi9LSBsYap1JvTC","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dkPxp1besOCsGRLY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-be-ta-czernin-the-noblewoman-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hpwNpiYcdbzVqyln","name":"Gréte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VIla8J2Kh6M6fjaF","name":"Gréte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96.","positive":"I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQcPYZe7Ufp4D1aq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-gr-te-96","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":96,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jtZTDUpXa8swDWBI","name":"Francesca Cantalupo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wXKAutPMQt3g6ENk","name":"Francesca Cantalupo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U5EySmYTUS4HVjtr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-francesca-cantalupo-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jx3IEo5q5hDiyR6v","name":"The Quiet Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gch41TwU0rKT3sjz","name":"The Quiet Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TQ8GE8X6XZ6rmTTO","name":"Gift - Quiet Guards","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5L0LXdcl2xkaDdXE","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-the-quiet-guards-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kRU4D9NcqLqeHvQw","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"GWRKVEgFAcvei4Lv","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","positive":"I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eSvDH8Y6SEV8Rpa7","name":"Gift - Stinking Survivor","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"88W9OnIhVgHmj4XK","name":"Gift - Safe Haven from the Maws","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"e4NNxQ9WEguSBwfj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-berend-the-crazed-captain-98","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":98,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"mKAuXdCBRpdu6J27","name":"Sailors","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KT5EPAdOnV8ctDgN","name":"Sailors - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bWx5wygaQpw9Vhoz","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-sailors-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"n3jxoVxBqZM9xIJi","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AHjDuOwvEUpocvFL","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"q0DMED0up3bhWf9E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-joanna-called-nana-the-servant-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uXiM3h3PQA4Ao1oD","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gw3FR42K16bZ0SFH","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111.","positive":"We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UKvi5szDeR5KnvGg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-karl-and-elsa-karenmann-111","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":111,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zdfOXbmT8p4Femcw","name":"The Prince","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7qnLrczUCVHVcSO","name":"The Prince - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KeYGTGNdtjOLEUv9","name":"Gift - Broken Heart","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"op3EcTxHv05yMVMf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-the-prince-172","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
